When I started Blush & Bowties a decade ago, I was actually working at a marketing company. During my short lived run working in an office, I met the incredible Caleigh who I've stayed friends with since. I'd had the absolute honour of helping plan 2 of her sister's weddings, so when the time came for Caleigh to tie the knot, I could not have been more excited. Caleigh and Jeff's vision was moody, dramatic and bold. And damn did we have fun making this vision come to life. Not only was this day beautiful, but getting to witness the two kindest, most loving and grateful souls soak up every minute, every second of their wedding day was a true reminder of why I do what I do, and what a freaking honour it is to help couple's make magic happen on their wedding day.

Closing the curtain on 2022 . . . it's been an eventful year and our team was happy to get back to a semi sense of normalcy with our weddings after 2 years of non-stop postponements and the immense challenges our industry faced. 

B & B turned 10 and it's wild to think back on where we started to where we are now. Helping plan stylish weddings with a modern and experience driven approach is a true honour we don't take lightly. This year we worked with so many couples who brought light, trust and pure joy to the process and we're forever grateful for those relationships and being part of their celebrations. We hold immense pride in the open heartnesses we bring to the table as creatives in this wild industry.

The one thing that really shifted for us this year was establishing a strong team, solidifying our roles in the company and owning that B & B is not a one woman show, we're a team and that is what makes us who we are and how we serve couples in our unique way. 

From the bottom of our hearts, thanks for following us along and your support. Wishing you a Happy New Year.

I'm very excited to announce the re-launch of the course I run for training wedding planners, The Modern Wedding Planners Collective!  Although I launched this course in spring 2020 (hmmmmm I wonder what big world event went down then . . . .) and although our worlds were turned upside down because of covid, I'm so thrilled we had so many amazing planners take the course and benefit from its teachings. Now with the wedding world FINALLY coming back to some sort of normalcy, we've spent the last 6 months rejuvenating the course and updating the content. 

When I launched my wedding planning business, Blush & Bowties, I felt confused and lost in a sea of competition. Pricing, services, systems, styling, branding, marketing - where to begin? But after many years of trial and error, I carved a clear path and presence in the wedding community. I built a six-figure wedding business with a focus on stylish, innovative, and thoughtfully curated celebrations with character. 

It’s taken me thousands of hours, tireless trial and error, and true dedication to build a successful approach for planning and designing weddings. In this course, I share the secrets behind my business, systems, templates, and my detailed approach to developing a unique presence as a wedding creative. I’m revealing the inner workings of my brand and business, in the hopes to help save you money, time, and wasted energy. 

The course includes 14 modules, live video training, 100 + essential templates (aka how I run my business), exercises and checklists, 175 page workbooking . . . seriously we've got you covered. 

We're celebrating the re-launch with a time sensitive 15% off discount. Use the code save15 in the month of January. 

No time like the present! If you have questions on the course you can email us at info@blushandbowties.ca

Happy Friday! Running Blush & Bowties for the past 10 years has opened doors of opportunity to other avenues I am interested in, one of them being education for planners. When I launched my wedding planning business a decade ago, I felt confused and lost in a sea of competition. Pricing, services, systems, styling, branding, marketing - where to begin? But after many years of trial and error, I carved a clear path and presence in the wedding world. I launched The Modern Wedding Planner's Collective to provide training that takes the guesswork out of how to run a wedding planning business. 

Since launching the MWPC (which began as a workshop and evolved into an in depth online course), I've helped over a 100 aspiring planners on their path to running a successful wedding planning business, and it's been a true labour of love to keep this course growing and alive. 

If you're interested in the course check out the link in our bio!

Happy love day! V-day marks the perfect occasion to do a little intro for those of you wondering about our vibe. We've been planning weddings for over a decade and our team consists of open hearted creatives with an unwavering dedication to the art of wedding planning and design. We approach wedding planning with an experience driven process and affinity for contemporary and timeless design. 

A big part of what defines our process is that we don't play into the traditional wedding tropes. Let's be real, sometimes weddings can come with a lot of baggage, opinions and expectations. Your wedding will be rad and meaningful, but we're just not into the notion of trying to outdo someone else's wedding, trying to impress your guests (our vibe is taking care of your people) and we certainly aren't here for feeding into the unrealistic expectation that a wedding day is supposed to be "perfect". Perfect doesn't exist. A room full of love, a seamless execution of your timeline, booking vendors who genuinely care about what they do, thoughtful design - these are the types of things we believe in. 

Will we work our buns off to create, design and run a freaking wondrous celebration? You betcha. Your wedding experience is what you make it and we love working with clients who connect with the heart of what a wedding is VS societal expectations. 

Sound like your thing? Amazing. If you are looking for a planner for this year we've got 3 spots open and we've opened up our calendar for 2024!

✨ Wedding trends for 2024? ✨

👉 Focus on taking care of your guests versus impressing them.

👉 Stop worrying about trends and what’s “in”.

👉 Consider experience versus expectations

For all you engaged people out there, we understand the pressure a wedding can bring and the inundation of wedding inspiration. Hey, we love stylish and amazing weddings - in fact, that is what we are dedicated to. But it’s easy to get swept up in all the planning and lose sight of why your wedding is important. If you like a current trend - do it! If you think champagne towers are weird - skip it! If you want to tie velvet bows to your candles because you think it’s the prettiest thing you’ve ever seen - cool! Go for it. Just do a little check-in with yourself and try to make decisions that feel connected to YOU and your partner.
